name: Comatose Vision Originals #1
description: This photograph is very meaningful to me. It was created 100% in-camera in 2005. (no Photoshop! only minimal Lightroom editing, a little contrast, a little noise reduction, a little contrast) I was recovering from having died and been in a coma I was not supposed to wake up from. I fought for my life for 6 months on insane amounts of oxycontin to manage the pain I was in. My world was a blur from the opiates, and I used the creative rush to make a series of abstract photos that mirrored what my world looked like in that drugged up state. I call the collection 'Comatose Vision'
